1.title: Spic 'n' Span
1.plot: Comet and friends learn working together is the best way to get a job done when they have to clean up after a messy group of customers.

2.title: Smoothie Operator
2.plot: A banana shortage forces Comet to try a new type of smoothie. He refuses at first, but when he tries is, he likes it.

3.title: Take Off!
3.plot: A broken ship forces Comet to miss a competition he was sure he was going to win. His friends team up to recreate the experience for him.

4.title: Oh, Brother!
4.plot: Comet's older brother Flash stops by--and shakes up the snack shack by forcing everyone to do their jobs faster. Comet questions his skills as a leader before standing up for himself and taking back control of the ship.

5.title: Bend It Like Radar
5.plot:

6.title: Lost and Found
6.plot: Halley calls a frustrated Comet to help find her lost key-- in the process Comet loses his own key and learns not to make friends feel bad about their mistakes.

7.title: I'll Save You
7.plot: Comet gets on everyone's nerves emulating his favorite superhero - until he actually saves his friends from danger.

8.title: Growin' Crazy
8.plot: Taking care of Sputnik's peach tree proves hard for Comet, who ends up feeding it too much fertilizer. The tree takes over the ship until Sputnik gets it under control.

9.title: Twice the Talent
9.plot: The crew decides to host a talent show--but not everyone's confident in their ability to perform. Sputnik and Comet try teaming up, but it turns out collaboration is more complicated than it sounds.

10.title: Building the Perfect Present
10.plot: When Comet sees everyone else's complicated presents for Sputnik's birthday, he tries to compete. But it turns out a simple, heartfelt present is better.

11.title: Glippi's Visit
11.plot: Sputnik is excited to host her pen pal, Glippi, at the space station, but Comet blows her tame, quiet plans with some louder, rowdier things he likes. At first the friends clash-- but soon learn about how to make sure new friends have fun.

12.title: Don't Touch
12.plot: Radar breaks a toy Comet treasures. He tries everything to avoid admitting it, but eventually comes clean.

13.title: Are You My Piffin?
13.plot: Halley discovers an adorable baby piffin, and the whole crew falls in love with the lost little guy. Radar becomes especially close to their new friend-- he even campaigns to keep him at the space station.

14.title: Halley's Wannabe
14.plot: When Sputnik takes a ride on one of Halley's Starscreamer surfboards, she thinks Halley is the greatest and begins to imitate everything she does. Sal helps Sputnik discover how her own qualities make her special and important, too.

15.title: Sputnik the Spoiler
15.plot: An overly-excited Sputnik shares her thoughts on the endings of movies, books, and games--taking all the fun out of them for her friends. In the end she learns that everyone has more fun if you avoid spoilers.

16.title: Don't Fear the Surfboard
16.plot: Halley's late with a large order of smoothies--leaving her questioning her job performance--and refusing to surf. But the crew steps up to show her she's skilled, and pretty soon she's back on her board.

17.title: Billy Starrider
17.plot: Radar gets a little too enthusiastic about Billy Starrider--refusing to play other games with his friends, and forcing them to play along with his imaginary world. His friends team up to show him that it's important to find a balance.

18.title: Sore Loser
18.plot: When Comet beats Radar at one of his favorite games, Radar turns out to be a sore loser--and an even more unpleasant winner! His friends help him learn that winning isn't everything.

19.title: Halley Goes Solo
19.plot: Halley steps up to run the Frosty Star alone, with the help of a new one-man smoothie-making machine. She's excited to show off her solo-smoothie-making skills, but when the café is overrun with customers, it's unclear if she'll succeed.

20.title: Z-Max Mania
20.plot:
Know what this is about?
 Be the first one to add a plot.

21.title: What a Mess
21.plot: Radar forgets to clean up after himself--frustrating the crew and turning the station into a mess! When he can't find all the parts of a game to play with two visiting friends, he takes action--and learns it's important to be responsible for your stuff.

22.title: Beck and Call
22.plot: Halley twists her ankle, and enjoys being taken care of by the rest of the crew- maybe a little TOO much. When her ankle starts to get better, she fakes the injury for a little longer until a trip to the Pingo Pongian Water Park motivates her to come clean.

23.title: Sputnik Takes Charge
23.plot: Inspired by a glossy magazine, Sputnik gives the café a makeover--reorganizing the kitchen and throwing a wrench in the crew's workflow. The crew must decide how to confront Sputnik--learning in this case, honesty is the best policy.

24.title: The Clean Machine
24.plot: Sal invents a cleaning robot, and the crew can't wait to try it out. But when Sal leaves to visit his GamGam, a series of machine mishaps ensues...leaving Comet & Co. to figure out a solution.

25.title: Comet's Gift
25.plot: The whole crew's excited about a secret gift exchange--except for Comet, who loves his gift so much he doesn't want to give it away. But when he sees how much joy it brings a friend, Comet learns that giving is the greatest joy of all.

26.title: A Star Is Born
26.plot: Team Astroblast puts on a show, and Comet learns a lesson about upstaging his friends.

27.title: A Bird in the Hand
27.plot: When Sputnik sees a mysterious bird, she has trouble convincing the rest of the crew that it's real.

28.title: How Do You Get to Carnegie Nebula? Practice, Practice, Practice
28.plot: Comet learns playing a musical instrument well takes a lot of work when the crew decides to put on a concert for their customers.

29.title: Who Let the Stuffie Out
29.plot: Comet is embarrassed when he drops his favorite stuffed animal in front of the whole café, but he learns he's not the only one with a cuddly toy.

30.title: Lights Out
30.plot: When Comet and Halley pull an all-nighter to play a new game, they learn they aren't quite themselves without a good night's sleep.

31.title: Shape Up
31.plot: Radar thinks techy gadgets are the best way to move around and get things done, but he learns that physical activity is essential to a healthy, happy lifestyle.

32.title: Surfin' Space Safari
32.plot: Neutrino goes missing--and Halley assumes her super cool new surfing friends accidentally took her favorite surfboard with them. She and Comet track them down, only to learn jumping to conclusions is a bad idea.

33.title: I Love a Parade... Sometimes
33.plot: Comet and the crew are psyched for a float-building competition, but they have trouble making a plan...especially since Comet has too many ideas.

34.title: Radar Sleeps Over
34.plot: Radar seems excited for a sleepover, but when it comes time to leave, his anticipation turns to anxiety. Radar's friends help him overcome his fears--and he ends up having a blast!

35.title: Stop Booging Me
35.plot: The crew is a little leery of Comet's insect-like Veezleboog collection, but when they learn about the cool things Veezleboogs can do, they welcome them into the Astroblast eco system.

36.title: Just Peachy
36.plot: When Sputnik's prized giant peach disappears from the Frosty Star, she puts on her detective hat and interviews all the suspects. No one is safe from suspicion...until Sputnik learns she shouldn't have jumped to conclusions.

37.title: Hole in One
37.plot: A mini golf competition pits fiercely competitive Sputnik and Jet against each other. But when they sacrifice their friendship for the game, they learn nothing is more important than your friends.

38.title: Treasure Hunt
38.plot: When the crew hears a story about hidden treasure in the Frosty Star, they all work together to reach the treasure chest.

39.title: Something Borrowed, Someone Blue
39.plot: Comet's brand new space pod is the fastest in the galaxy--and all his friends want to borrow it. When he lends it to them, his friends try to take care of it, but they can't live up to Comet's exacting demands.

40.title: Be Mine
40.plot: A mailbox mixup leaves Comet questioning his friendship with Halley--and refusing to ask her what's going on. Eventually he learns communicating about a problem is the best way to figure it out.

41.title: GamGam Knows Best
41.plot: When the crew meets Sal's GamGam, they're shocked at how fragile she seems. But when she saves the day, they learn that they jumped to conclusions about what she could do.

42.title: Three's a Crowd
42.plot: Halley and Sputnik are BFFEEs until Sputnik takes up a new hobby with Jet, and Halley gets jealous of all the time they're spending together. It takes time, and feelings get hurt, but they learn other friends and interests are an important part of a healthy friendship.

43.title: Who's Afraid of the Big Bad Alligator
43.plot: A family of new customers are scared of Jet, but they learn to trust him after he saves the littlest one from a fall.

44.title: Sing Along to the Bouncing Monkey
44.plot: When Radar gets obsessed with the new karaoke machine Comet got for a party, he doesn't want to give anyone else a turn.

45.title: I Feel Fine
45.plot: Sputnik's so excited for a Carly Cosmos concert, she tries to hid the fact that she's sick. But her friends catch on and make her rest--and even bring the fun back home!

46.title: Shoes Blues
46.plot: Jet's favorite sneakers are on their last leg, but he loves them too much to get new ones--even though they're too small and prevent him from playing soccer. His friends help him navigate his feelings and soon he's back on his feet--in some shiny new shoes.

47.title: Radar for a Day
47.plot: Halley thinks Radar is taking his time fixing something for her, but when she tries to take over his job, she learns she underestimated it.

48.title: A Gift from Halley
48.plot: Halley gives Comet a gift--but when he can't figure out what it is, he worries that he'll hurt her feelings.

49.title: Best Guests
49.plot: The crew can't agree on how to show their customers they care--they try putting on a parade, building a ride, and making the galaxy's biggest smoothie. All these complicated ideas aren't so easy to execute. In the end they learn it's the thought that counts, not how complicated the event is.

50.title: Puzzle Hunt
50.plot: The crew stumbles on a scavenger hunt on a lazy afternoon in the Frosty Star. It isn't long before they're working together and using their senses and problem solving skills to piece the clues together.

51.title: Bop Til You Drop
51.plot: Some tiny, cute Bippity-Bop customers stop by the Frosty Star...and multiply every time they drink a smoothie. Soon the café is over-run with them, and the crew has to figure out how to take control.

52.title: Kapowsers!
52.plot: The Frosty Star garners some attention--the smoothies are the best in the galaxy! But when reporters come to interview the crew, they act differently in front of the cameras. In the end, they learn it's always better to be yourself.

imdb.plot outline: Run by a cast of animal characters including Comet, Halley, Sputnik, Radar, Jet and Sal the Octopus, the Astroblast! Space Station is the coolest hangout in the galaxy. Through the crew's friendship, the series imparts important messages about how to embrace differences, model positive relationships and foster healthy habits to be the best good-will ambassadors in the universe.
